nction fills the editor windowK			removes all point except the first+			zoom out-			zoom ing			show/hide the grid->			time-stretch the selected points<-			time-contract the selected pointsup-arrow		stretch the values of the selected pointsdown-arrow		contract the values of the selected pointstab			change to another edit mode following the sequence 			(edit - zoom - sel - drag ...)a			add another BPF to the editors			select  one BPF d			deletes the selected BPF"))))